x4freetext: For the 130 MeV, experiment the
tritons were detected and identified with a 1 mm
thick Si surface barrier dE detector and a 15-mm thick
Ortec high-purity Ge E detector.
The experiment at 170 MeV used a
stack of two 13-mm thick high-purity Ge detectors
Since this experiment was planned as a target survey,
only a few angles were measured for each target.
Those fragmentary angular distributions are shown in
Fig. 8 to give the reader an idea of the size
of the cross sections. => in REACTION code SF8=MSC.
Digitizing error for data 5%.

x4freetext: Uncertainty in the cross section value,
